ometry of the universe, and how they offer a blueprint for the formation of cosmic structure.Not only does Page explain current observations and measurements, he describes how they can be woven together into a unified picture to form the Standard Model of Cosmology. Yet much remains unknown, and this incisive book also describes the search for ever deeper knowledge at the field's frontiers-from quests to understand the nature of neutrinos and dark energy to investigations into the physics of the very early universe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSCIENCE / Cosmology.2bisacsh  aA Brief History of Time.  aAlbert Einstein.  aAlex Vilenkin.  aAn Astronomer's Guide.  aArno Allan Penzias.  aBernhard Riemann.  aCMB anisotropy.  aCosmology for the Curious.  aDelia Perlov.  aHubble space telescope.  aJames Peebles.  aJer Yu.  aJo Dunkley.  aMax Planck.  aMilky Way.  aNASA.  aOur Universe.  aPlanck map.  aPlanck satellite.  aPlanck space telescope.  aRashid Sunyaev.  aRobert Woodrow Wilson.  aStephen Hawking.  aWMAP satellite.  aZel'dovich.  ablackbodies.  ablackbody radiation.  acosmological constant.  adark energy.  adark matter.  aelectromagnetic spectrum.  athe expanding universe.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishz978311070475408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069008840uhttps://do